						<summary>

						

						<p><hi rend="bold">Śaka 1474 (1552 A.D.)</hi></p>						

						<p>Damaged. Seems to refer to an endowment of money made by Kuruchēṭi Śrīraṅgarāja to the shrine of Kūrattāḻvār. The details of date viz. <hi rend="bold">Śaka 1474 Paridhāvin, Srāvaṇa ba. Srījayanti correspond to 1552 A.D., Āugust 12, (Friday), ·78; f.d.n. 21.</hi> A fragment probably connected with this mentions Nārayyaṅgāru of Puttūr as one of the purchasers of <hi rend="italic">vṛittis</hi> in Pērāṅgiyūru.</p>						

						</summary>
